5.	They answer your prospectâ€™s question about what theyâ€™ll have to do (CONDITIONS).
6.	They tell your prospect how youâ€™ll back up the PROMISE youâ€™ve made to them (RISK REMOVAL).
The rest of your sales letter copy will simply restate, reinforce, and reassure your prospect of these six things. 
Formula #4: The Pain to Promise Opening
This opening is nearly identical to the Bold Promise Opening, with one extra detail. Youâ€™ll start by asking them three questions or making three statements that confirm their experience with the SYMPTOMS of the PROBLEM. 
These questions can start with "Have you decidedâ€¦" or â€œAre you readyâ€¦" or â€œWhat is ___, doing to yourâ€¦â€ or â€œCan you really afford to keepâ€¦â€ and finish with a description of one of the SYMPTOMS of your prospectâ€™s PROBLEM. 
********************************EXAMPLE********************************
