Next, use a statement that starts with â€œThatâ€™s whyâ€¦â€ or â€œThankfullyâ€¦â€ followed by a short description of how your product or service was specifically made for your prospectâ€™s demographic. Finish this paragraph with a â€œThis meansâ€¦â€ statement about how your OFFER delivers the PROMISE by the DEADLINE, without the EXTERNAL OBJECTION and despite the INTERNAL OBJECTION.
Next, use a statement that starts with â€œThatâ€™s what makes [PRODUCT]...â€ or â€œThis is why [PRODUCT]â€¦â€ and reaffirms the exact statement made in your first sentence. For example, you might say â€œThatâ€™s what makes [PRODUCT] is best (see my Super Seven in Chapter XI) for [AUDIENCE] who want [PROMISE]...â€ or â€œThis is the first reason [AUDIENCE] prefer [PRODUCT] for [PROMISE].â€
Youâ€™ve now demonstrated the Demographic Relevance of your product or service. 
Next, youâ€™ll demonstrate Psychographic Relevance with another subheader (or callout). This one will tell our AUDIENCE how our product or service aligns with either their shopping preferences or the ideological values. For example, this headline appeals to shopping preferences:
Your Convenience is Our Top Priority
If convenience is the top priority for my AUDIENCE, this headline ^ is perfect. If they prefer fast results or delivery, I might say something like this instead:
