Element #5: Qualification
Qualification raises the perception of your product or service to the ceiling. The formula is simple, and based on reverse psychology. In sales, this is called a â€œTake Away.â€ I dislike that term because, in my opinion, Qualification should be exactly that. It should put up a big, bold stop sign telling your prospect who you want to do business with. Itâ€™s a mistake to assume that you should sell to anyone willing to buy from you. Some customers are more trouble than theyâ€™re worth, and others will literally be a drain on your profits. Thatâ€™s the first practical reason for including a Qualification Pitch. 
The second reason is that it truly does elevate the perceived value of your product or service. Most people want something more the second they realize they canâ€™t have it. 
Start your Qualification Pitch with a direct command for your prospect to stop and pay attention. Tie this to a statement about them saying yes to your OFFER. For example, your stop command might look like this:
â—	Wait! Before You Order
â—	STOP! Before You Sign Up
â—	WARNING: Read This Before You Apply
