Post CTA 
Post CTA Prompt:
Now use the variables and subvariables to write our Post CTA message. This Post CTA message MUST be consistent with whatâ€™s in the copy weâ€™ve already created for this funnel. Please use the content in the article below as a guide in creating my Post CTA message. 
www.sethczerepak.com/urgency-in-copywriting
This Post CTA message should focus on internal pressure rather than external pressure. Internal pressure is based on what psychologists call â€œcognitive dissonance.â€ Cognitive dissonance is that uncomfortable feeling you get when you hold contradictory beliefs, ideas, feelings, or values. Cognitive dissonance theory states that people may change their attitude or their behavior to relieve themselves from this psychological discomfort. Your job is to create cognitive dissonance in your prospect using a Post CTA message that contrasts the emotional pain of your prospectâ€™s PROBLEM with the emotional benefit of your PROMISE. 
Start your Post CTA message with a double tie down style subheader like one of these:
1.	Isnâ€™t It Time to Stop [PROBLEM], and Start [PROMISE]?
2.	Isnâ€™t It Time to Start [PROMISE], and Stop [PROBLEM]?
3.	Havenâ€™t You Waited Long Enough for [PROMISE]?
4.	Havenâ€™t You Suffered from [PROBLEM] Long Enough?
Next, use a statement like â€œYou want [PROMISE]â€¦â€ or â€œYouâ€™ve read this far because you want [PROMISE].â€ Then, use a statement like â€œBy now, you know that there are only two choices leftâ€¦â€ followed by a summary of their two choices: 
1.	The PROBLEM and its pain points
2.	Your PROMISE and its benefits
Next, take a shot at the negatives of doing nothing (MYTHS, MISTAKES, or ALTERNATIVES [whichever you covered earlier in your funnel]), with a statement like â€œForget all theâ€¦â€ or â€œNo more wasting time withâ€¦â€ followed by a list of the negative things theyâ€™re struggling with now. 
Next, confirm that none of these things matter if they donâ€™t have the advantage that your product or service USP gives them. Take three shots at these MYTHS, MISTAKES, or ALTERNATIVES by highlighting their ongoing negative impact. 
Next, remind them of the physical, financial, social, and/or emotional cost theyâ€™ve already suffered as a result of the above things. Add a statement like â€œyouâ€™re running out of (time, money, opportunity, etc.)â€¦â€ statement to remind them of how relevant, critical, and urgent the PROBLEM is and the CRISIS it will inevitably lead to. 
Next, use a question to confirm whether they still want to solve the PROBLEM and experience the PROMISE, without the EXTERNAL OBJECTION, and despite the INTERNAL OBJECTION. Here are some examples of this kind of question:
â—	Want to get unstuck and explode your income? 
â—	Isnâ€™t it time to rid yourself of pain and stiffness for good?
â—	Ready to finally experience the loving marriage you deserve?
Next, give your prospect a direct command or suggestion to take ACTION, and tie this to the PROMISE and the DEADLINE. Follow this with another reminder of the high cost (in time, money, energy, health, emotional pain, etc.) of doing nothing, continuing what theyâ€™re doing now, and/or experimenting with the ALTERNATIVES or trying to get the result themselves. 
Next, use a statement like â€œOne you [ACTION]â€¦â€ or â€œAs soon as you [ACTION]â€¦â€ or â€œThe moment you [ACTION]â€¦â€ followed by a future pacing of them owning and/or using your product or service, and experiencing the PROMISE within the DEADLINE. 
Next, use a â€œOther [SOLUTION], will claim [competitorâ€™s claims here], but how many will [your GUARANTEE here]?â€ Answer this question with a clear and bold claim that your competitor simply canâ€™t offer the same USP, PROMISE, and/or GUARANTEE. 
Next, plant a splinter in their mind with a statement like â€œNow that you know thisâ€¦youâ€™llâ€¦â€ or â€œNow that youâ€™ve read thisâ€¦youâ€™llâ€¦â€ or â€œNow that you know how to [PROMISE]â€¦youâ€™llâ€¦â€ followed by a embedded hypnotic suggestion about your OFFER and/or message sticking in their memory. 
Add a statement like â€œYouâ€™ll think about this every time youâ€¦â€ followed by a word picture of their experience with the PROBLEM or their frustrations with the SOLUTION. Finish with a statement like â€œItâ€™s time to stop [PROBLEM] and [PROMISE] so you can [physical, financial, social and/or emotional benefit].â€
********************************EXAMPLE********************************
Isnâ€™t It Time To Break Your Income Plateau?
