The caveat is that the next level promise should be something your prospect can easily see and understand. If the connection between your original PROMISE and your next level promise is obvious, your upsell will be much more persuasive. If not, your prospect will ignore your upsell, or tell themselves that theyâ€™ll try it later if they like your original OFFER. 
Start this message with a headline that links your original PROMISE to your next level promise. For extra effect, add the deadline of your next level promise, and the EXTERNAL OBJECTION. Iâ€™ve done both of these in the example below. 
Next, reaffirm the PROMISE you made with your original OFFER. Then, use a statement like â€œNow imagineâ€¦â€ followed by a description of the next level promise and its physical, financial, social, and/or emotional benefits. 
