In case youâ€™re unfamiliar, a hat-in-the-hand close is a term coined by the sales legend Zig Ziglar. Zig was a door to door salesman who would make a downsell offer at the last minute, just as he was putting his hat back on and preparing to leave the prospectâ€™s house. Hence the term â€œhat-in-the-hand close.â€ Just be sure that your sales staff donâ€™t use this downsell as a crutch, and only after their prospect has said a hard and definite no. 
